The paper focuses on improving the accuracy of lower-precision arithmetic types for solving Ordinary Differential Equations (ODEs) in the domain of neuroscience. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of stochastic rounding and fixed-point arithmetic, which are relevant to the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.MS) and Architecture (cs.AR). The paper also mentions the solution of Partial Differential Equations (PDEs), which falls under the sub-categories of Systems and Control (cs.SY) and Scientific Computing (cs.SC).
